This paper is about a policy mining algorithm for relationship-based access control (ReBAC), which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The algorithm uses a neural network for feature selection, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the scalability and extensibility of the algorithm, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG), software engineering (cs.SE), and databases (cs.DB).
